      "content": "So you're saying the negative effects basically don't exist? That seems like a pretty bold claim considering so many people are seeing higher rents and crowded schools in areas with high immigration. Is there really no valid economic case for restricting immigration, or is there just a consensus that it's always good for the economy?",
